# Evolution API Client Standards

## Client wrapper
```typescript
// apps/worker/src/evolution/client.ts
export class EvolutionClient {
  constructor(
    private readonly baseUrl: string,  // sem barra final
    private readonly apiKey: string,   // descriptografado
  ) {}

  private get headers() {
    return { 'apikey': this.apiKey, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' };
  }

  async getConnectionState(instanceName: string): Promise<ConnectionStateResult> {
    const encoded = encodeURIComponent(instanceName);
    const response = await fetchWithTimeout(
      `${this.baseUrl}/instance/connectionState/${encoded}`,
      { headers: this.headers },
      5_000 // ping timeout
    );
    return this.parseConnectionState(response);
  }

  async setPresence(instanceName: string): Promise<PresenceResult> {
    const encoded = encodeURIComponent(instanceName);
    const response = await fetchWithTimeout(
      `${this.baseUrl}/instance/setPresence/${encoded}`,
      { method: 'POST', headers: this.headers, body: JSON.stringify({ presence: 'available' }) },
      5_000
    );
    return this.parsePresence(response);
  }

  async restart(instanceName: string): Promise<void> {
    const encoded = encodeURIComponent(instanceName);
    await fetchWithTimeout(
      `${this.baseUrl}/instance/restart/${encoded}`,
      { method: 'POST', headers: this.headers },
      10_000 // restart timeout
    );
  }

  async getConnectQR(instanceName: string, phoneNumber?: string): Promise<QRResult> {
    const encoded = encodeURIComponent(instanceName);
    const url = phoneNumber
      ? `${this.baseUrl}/instance/connect/${encoded}?number=${phoneNumber}`
      : `${this.baseUrl}/instance/connect/${encoded}`;
    const response = await fetchWithTimeout(url, { headers: this.headers }, 10_000);
    return this.parseQR(response);
  }

  async fetchInstances(): Promise<EvolutionInstance[]> {
    const response = await fetchWithTimeout(
      `${this.baseUrl}/instance/fetchInstances`,
      { headers: this.headers },
      10_000
    );
    if (!response.ok) throw new AppError('NETWORK_ERROR', 'Failed to fetch instances');
    return response.json();
  }
}
```

## Health check duplo — AMBOS devem passar
```typescript
export async function checkInstanceHealth(number: NumberWithProject): Promise<HealthResult> {
  const client = new EvolutionClient(
    number.project.evolutionUrl,
    decrypt(number.project.evolutionApiKey)
  );

  // Step 1: connectionState
  const stateResult = await client.getConnectionState(number.instanceName);
  if (stateResult.errorType) {
    return { healthy: false, errorType: stateResult.errorType };
  }
  if (stateResult.state !== 'open') {
    return { healthy: false, errorType: 'UNKNOWN', detail: `state=${stateResult.state}` };
  }

  // Step 2: setPresence (apenas se state=open)
  const presenceResult = await client.setPresence(number.instanceName);
  if (!presenceResult.ok) {
    return { healthy: false, errorType: presenceResult.errorType ?? 'UNKNOWN' };
  }

  return { healthy: true };
}
```

## Parsing das respostas da Evolution
```typescript
// connectionState response: { instance: { state: 'open' | 'close' | 'connecting' } }
// OU (versões antigas): { state: 'open' | ... } no topo
private parseConnectionState(response: Response, body: unknown): ConnectionStateResult {
  if (!response.ok) {
    return { state: null, errorType: classifyEvolutionError(response, body) };
  }
  const state = (body as any)?.instance?.state ?? (body as any)?.state;
  return { state: state?.toLowerCase() ?? null, errorType: null };
}

// setPresence: sucesso = HTTP 201 e body NÃO contém 'close'
private parsePresence(response: Response, body: unknown): PresenceResult {
  if (response.status !== 201) {
    return { ok: false, errorType: classifyEvolutionError(response, body) };
  }
  const bodyStr = JSON.stringify(body).toLowerCase();
  if (bodyStr.includes('close')) {
    return { ok: false, errorType: 'UNKNOWN' };
  }
  return { ok: true };
}

// connect response: { pairingCode, base64, code, count }
// OU (algumas versões): { qrcode: { base64 } }
private parseQR(response: Response, body: unknown): QRResult {
  const b = body as any;
  const qrBase64 = b?.base64 ?? b?.qrcode?.base64 ?? null;
  const pairingCode = b?.pairingCode ?? null;
  return { qrBase64, pairingCode };
}
```

## instanceName encoding
- SEMPRE usar `encodeURIComponent(instanceName)` na URL
- instanceName pode ter espaços e caracteres especiais
- O nome na Evolution é case-sensitive — guardar exatamente como vem da fetchInstances

## Evolution v2 — token por instância no restart

- `GET /instance/fetchInstances` com a **API key global** do projeto retorna linhas com `instanceName`/`name` e **`token`** por instância.
- No monitor: persistir o token cifrado em **`Number.evolutionInstanceApiKey`** ao aplicar sync (`NumberService.applySyncFromEvolution`); atualizar o campo quando o sync for refeito e o token vier na lista.
- **`POST /instance/restart/:name`**: usar o **token da instância** no header `apikey`, não a key global. `EvolutionClient.restart(instanceName, { instanceApiKey })` e `resolveInstanceToken(instanceName)` (v2: `fetchInstances` + parse) em `packages/shared/src/evolution/client.ts`.
- Worker `restart`: se não houver token no DB, resolver com `resolveInstanceToken`, persistir, depois reiniciar; se ainda não houver token, falhar com erro explícito (não usar key global no restart).

## Evolution Go (`EvolutionFlavor.EVOLUTION_GO`)

Implementação real: `packages/shared/src/evolution/client.ts` (opção `flavor` no construtor).

- **Listar instâncias**: `GET /instance/all` (não `/instance/fetchInstances`).
- **Token por instância**: com a API key global, `GET /instance/all` → localizar `name` → usar `token` como header `apikey` para `GET /instance/status` e `GET /instance/qr`.
- **Saúde**: `Connected` e `LoggedIn` verdadeiros no corpo (envelope `data`); sem `connectionState`/`setPresence` da v2.
- **Restart**: não existe na API Go — `restart()` falha; worker `restart` ignora Go; health-check alerta na **primeira** falha (sem fila restart).
